+ You are using scriptlets. As per [documentation][1]:

&gt;  Because scriptlet code executes before the page is served, it can
&gt; only run once per page;

This means that if your spreadsheet data changes, your html table will not incorporate the change.

+ The Apps Script [onChange][2] trigger can run an Apps Script code, fired by a change in the document. However, I assume that you are deploying a Web App, and the WebApp will not be updated by an onChange trigger, unless you refresh your browser manually.

+ For your situation you best bet would be to use [polling][3] for refreshing the data in your website in combination with [google.script.run][4]

**Sample:**

